[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":97},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F21\u002Fjsweirdworld-45-objects-functions-chapter-wrapup\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F21\u002Fjsweirdworld-45-objects-functions-chapter-wrapup\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F21\u002Fjsweirdworld-45-objects-functions-chapter-wrapup\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F21\u002Fjsweirdworld-45-objects-functions-chapter-wrapup\u002F":73,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F21\u002Fjsweirdworld-45-objects-functions-chapter-wrapup\u002F":82},"\u002Fjsweirdworld\u002F20190521\u002F2581746580\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":55,"date":56,"description":57,"extension":58,"lang":59,"meta":60,"navigation":61,"path":62,"readingMinutes":63,"seo":64,"standalone":65,"stem":66,"tags":67,"tldr":70,"updated":56,"url":71,"__hash__":72},"content\u002Fen\u002FJsWeirdWorld\u002Fjsweirdworld-45-objects-functions-chapter-wrapup.md","[JS Weird World] No.45 Wrapping Up the Objects & Functions Chapter","1000308844",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":49},"minimark",[11,16,24,27,30,33,36,40],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"wrapping-up-the-objects-functions-chapter","Wrapping up the Objects & Functions chapter",[17,18,19],"p",{},[20,21],"img",{"alt":22,"src":23},"Objects and functions chapter wrap-up","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FVHBwQzb.png",[17,25,26],{},"Honestly, for the longest time I never really had a solid grip on IIFEs and closures. I'd written a few posts that brushed up against them before, but something always felt a little off, you know?",[17,28,29],{},"And the idea that functions are objects in JavaScript? That never even crossed my mind until I dug into it properly. Let alone automatic semicolon insertion.",[17,31,32],{},"The last two lessons were actually really good. But honestly, I'm going to need to put in som